stimulusHtml: Which of the following factors is most important for the team to consider before drawing conclusions from the data?

features.html: A research team is analyzing survey data to determine the average number of hours high school students spend on homework each night. The survey was conducted online, and students volunteered to participate.Â

choicesHtml: The survey data are considered reliable because the survey used self-reported responses from students.
The survey results may not represent all high school students because only those with Internet access and interest in the topic participated.
The survey ensures accuracy because students were able to choose whether or not to participate.
The method of survey collection does not matter as long as there are a large number of responses in the data set.
